24:40.521 --> 24:42.690
‐ Yes, fuck, yes.
‐ Then I'll do it.

24:42.773 --> 24:45.192
I'll fuck up my hearing
so that I can stay with you.

24:45.275 --> 24:47.987
If that's what you want, fine.

24:49.363 --> 24:50.948
‐ Yeah, fine.
‐ Good.

24:51.031 --> 24:52.908
Good.

24:55.911 --> 24:57.079
[Liam]
<i>Hey, V, guess what.</i>

24:57.162 --> 24:58.789
I have a new black uncle.

24:58.872 --> 25:01.500
‐ You do?
‐ His name's MaVar.

25:01.583 --> 25:02.626
He's great.

25:02.710 --> 25:03.377
He's taking me
to the Sox/Cubs game.

25:03.460 --> 25:05.879
Wait a second.
Who is this guy?

25:05.963 --> 25:06.422
Used car salesman.

25:06.505 --> 25:08.382
Lives down the street.

25:08.465 --> 25:10.718
Used car salesman?
That's code for shady.

25:10.801 --> 25:11.885
He married?

25:11.969 --> 25:12.386
Got kids of his own?

25:12.469 --> 25:13.303
I think he's gay.

25:13.387 --> 25:15.723
And he dresses real slick.

25:15.806 --> 25:17.266
[phone chimes]

25:17.349 --> 25:19.685
He says I can bring a friend.

25:19.768 --> 25:20.728
Wanna come?

25:20.811 --> 25:21.979
No.
And neither should you.

25:22.062 --> 25:23.022
Stranger danger.

25:23.105 --> 25:23.731
V, you should go.

25:23.814 --> 25:24.523
You were just talking about

25:24.606 --> 25:26.483
how you need to
make new friends.

25:26.567 --> 25:27.276
And I think
a little gayboy car salesman

25:27.359 --> 25:29.278
sounds perfect for you.

25:29.361 --> 25:30.904
[Kermit]
My mom loves hers.

25:30.988 --> 25:31.989
Found him at Toyota.

25:32.072 --> 25:32.614
And it's the Cubs/Sox game.

25:32.698 --> 25:34.199
What do you have to lose?

25:38.412 --> 25:40.080
Fellow welders.

25:40.164 --> 25:43.333
Thank you all for joining me
and union Jerry here

25:43.417 --> 25:45.753
in this neutral,
non‐work‐related location.

25:45.836 --> 25:46.920
Have you all got fries?

25:47.004 --> 25:49.131
Perfect.

25:49.214 --> 25:50.132
I've done some Googling,

25:50.215 --> 25:52.092
and I've gotta warn you:

25:52.176 --> 25:54.970
what I'm about to say
is triggering.

25:55.054 --> 25:57.556
The plumbers get Easter off.

25:57.639 --> 25:58.599
They get Veterans Day off,

25:58.682 --> 26:00.392
Memorial Day, Labor Day,

26:00.476 --> 26:02.644
Fourth of July,
their birthdays,

26:02.728 --> 26:05.064
and get this:
Columbus Day,

26:05.147 --> 26:06.815
Farhad, take a wild guess.

26:06.899 --> 26:10.527
How many paid weeks off do you
think they get at Christmas?

26:10.611 --> 26:11.528
One?

26:11.612 --> 26:13.030
Three.

26:13.113 --> 26:15.699
Two for Christmas,
one for Hanukkah/Kwanzaa.

26:15.783 --> 26:17.409
They get sick days.

26:17.493 --> 26:21.080
They get dental,
including orthodontia.

26:21.163 --> 26:23.082
Look at this bitch.

26:23.165 --> 26:24.374
She has Invisalign.

26:25.417 --> 26:28.295
Now, do we believe in change?

26:28.378 --> 26:31.465
The rights of workers matter.

26:31.548 --> 26:34.593
Union Jerry, I would like
to commence a vote.

26:34.676 --> 26:35.969
To join the union!

26:36.053 --> 26:37.596
Who's with me?

26:37.679 --> 26:40.474
[workers murmuring]

26:43.977 --> 26:45.646
‐ [Anne] Sorry, I‐‐
‐ It's okay.

26:45.729 --> 26:46.188
I can wait outside
if you want.

26:46.271 --> 26:48.315
No, whatever.

26:48.398 --> 26:50.442
We're all adults here.

26:50.526 --> 26:52.402
So you all done for today?

26:52.486 --> 26:56.365
Uh, yeah,
because shift's over.

26:56.448 --> 26:57.616
Right.

26:57.699 --> 26:58.826
It was a dumb question anyway.

26:58.909 --> 26:59.910
Shift's over.

27:01.912 --> 27:03.038
You got anything going on
for the rest of the day?

27:03.122 --> 27:05.332
More work.

27:05.415 --> 27:07.459
Got my third job
with my family.

27:07.543 --> 27:10.045
My stupid cousin
threw his back out landscaping,

27:10.129 --> 27:12.631
so it's all hands on deck
for the family business.

27:12.714 --> 27:13.215
Oh, yeah?
You guys need a hand,

27:13.298 --> 27:16.009
I could come by.

27:16.093 --> 27:18.178
You would not last
an hour making tamales.

27:20.514 --> 27:22.641
Look, I don't mean
to straight‐up neg you,

27:22.724 --> 27:25.269
but FYI I'm not trying to be
some pirate's

27:25.352 --> 27:26.186
side‐piece this summer.

27:26.270 --> 27:28.814
I heard you say
you have a girlfriend.

27:28.897 --> 27:29.982
Yeah, so?

27:30.065 --> 27:32.025
I mean,
we can still be friends.

27:32.109 --> 27:33.360
We're vape partners,
Captain Bob associates.

27:33.443 --> 27:35.362
We should be able
to hang out.

27:35.445 --> 27:37.114
Plus I make dope tamales.

27:37.197 --> 27:38.949
You know how to make tamales?

27:39.032 --> 27:40.409
Oh, yeah.
Big time.

27:40.492 --> 27:41.451
Okay.

27:44.705 --> 27:46.874
[knock at door]

27:46.957 --> 27:48.000
[Dr. Drew]
Hey, sorry for the wait.

27:48.083 --> 27:50.210
A corgi came in with a cyst.

27:50.294 --> 27:52.880
Had to aspirate,
very stressful.

27:52.963 --> 27:55.215
So, Mikey.
How you feeling?

27:55.299 --> 27:56.216
Not good, doc.

27:56.300 --> 27:57.718
Ah, well, of course
you're not feeling well.

27:57.801 --> 27:59.136
You need dialysis.

27:59.219 --> 27:59.511
Were due days ago.

27:59.595 --> 28:00.470
Dialysis?

28:00.554 --> 28:03.307
Mm.
Kidney disease.

28:03.390 --> 28:04.683
End stage renal at this point.

28:04.766 --> 28:07.394
That's full kidney fail,
stage 5.

28:07.477 --> 28:08.729
You have kidney disease?

28:08.812 --> 28:10.814
I only have one kidney!

28:10.898 --> 28:12.441
We have so much in common.

28:12.524 --> 28:13.066
Okay.

28:13.150 --> 28:15.694
Here we go.

28:15.777 --> 28:16.653
Take your own temperature,
Mikey.

28:16.737 --> 28:18.697
You know the drill.

28:18.780 --> 28:21.366
Yeah, we do dialysis
every few weeks.

28:21.450 --> 28:22.409
It keeps him walking around.

28:22.492 --> 28:26.204
But this dialysis is for pets,

28:26.288 --> 28:28.415
So about an eighth
of the strength he needs.

28:28.498 --> 28:30.417
About ready?

28:30.500 --> 28:31.460
Let's see what we got.

28:31.543 --> 28:31.919
[gasps]

28:35.339 --> 28:37.257
Mm‐hmm.

28:37.341 --> 28:39.259
Mild fever.

28:39.343 --> 28:40.427
All right, well, let's, uh,
let's get that shirt off

28:40.510 --> 28:45.182
and hook up the port.

28:45.265 --> 28:46.767
‐ [both grunt]
‐ Up you go.

28:46.850 --> 28:48.018
‐ Oh, jeez.
‐ [Dr. Drew] Oh, Jesus.

28:48.101 --> 28:50.729
‐ Jesus H. Christ.
‐ Lucifer.

28:50.812 --> 28:52.064
Yeah, it's a little angry
right now.

28:52.147 --> 28:52.773
[Dr. Drew]
No, that is infected.

28:52.856 --> 28:55.108
Mikey, and maybe staph, too.

28:55.192 --> 28:56.818
Oh, god, what a stench.

28:56.902 --> 28:57.694
Like a can of tuna
in a hot car, buddy.

28:57.778 --> 29:00.822
That needs to be replaced
immediately,

29:00.906 --> 29:01.740
and that is
people‐doctor stuff, Mikey.

29:01.823 --> 29:03.742
You're gonna have to go
to an ER.

29:03.825 --> 29:07.120
That gonna cost a lot of
money, Doc?

29:07.204 --> 29:09.915
I have no idea.

29:09.998 --> 29:11.875
If you were a dog,
I'd recommend we put you down.

29:11.959 --> 29:12.751
Okay, I'll go.

29:12.834 --> 29:15.337
But could you just
do me a little

29:15.420 --> 29:17.798
doggie dialysis
right now, please?

29:17.881 --> 29:20.008
Do you have the 150
you owe me from last time?

29:20.092 --> 29:21.802
Aww, give the man
an hour on the machine!

29:21.885 --> 29:24.638
Payment is due
at time of service.

29:24.721 --> 29:28.225
150 from last time,
150 for today, 300 total.

29:28.308 --> 29:29.309
I can't do math, Doc.

29:29.393 --> 29:31.478
I'm sick!

29:31.561 --> 29:34.231
Okay,
you get that dialysis ready.

29:34.314 --> 29:36.149
We'll go visit
the Debbie ATM.

29:36.233 --> 29:38.443
Okay.
All right.

29:38.527 --> 29:39.736
‐ Oh.
‐ [Frank] There you go, buddy.

29:39.820 --> 29:41.154
Let's go.

29:41.238 --> 29:42.656
[dog whining]

29:50.080 --> 29:52.040
Hey.

29:52.124 --> 29:54.001
Look who's up and outta ICU!

29:54.084 --> 29:55.293
Hi.
[grunts]

29:55.377 --> 29:56.169
‐ How's she doing?
‐ Good.

29:56.253 --> 29:58.755
Blood pressure's
only slightly elevated.

29:58.839 --> 30:00.549
177 over 122.

30:00.632 --> 30:01.591
[Lip]
That's good.

30:01.675 --> 30:04.678
‐ Hi, you.
‐ Hi, you.

30:04.761 --> 30:07.639
Getting better
one day at a time.

30:07.723 --> 30:10.684
And one fart conversation
at a time.

30:10.767 --> 30:12.102
I swear to Christ,
a doctor asks me every

30:12.185 --> 30:12.978
20 minutes
if I've passed gas,

30:13.061 --> 30:14.980
'cause apparently
that's how they know

30:15.063 --> 30:16.565
if my abdomen
is permanently severed.

30:16.648 --> 30:18.608
‐ All right.
‐ [laughs]

30:18.692 --> 30:19.609
Ooh, did you bring my shampoo?

30:19.693 --> 30:20.861
‐ Oh, no.

30:20.944 --> 30:22.195
But I brought you
something better.

30:22.279 --> 30:24.448
[Tami] You did?
What?

30:24.531 --> 30:27.159
[sighs]
Ta‐da!

30:27.242 --> 30:28.994
[laughs]

30:30.537 --> 30:31.913
Thought that now that
you're out of ICU,

30:31.997 --> 30:33.874
you might like to try
some skin‐to‐skin.

30:33.957 --> 30:36.501
What do you think, buddy?
Huh?

30:36.585 --> 30:37.711
Hey, hey.

30:41.214 --> 30:42.299
Hey, what's wrong?

30:42.382 --> 30:43.925
[sighs]

30:44.009 --> 30:45.427
Sorry.

30:45.510 --> 30:48.388
He's just
so beautiful,

30:48.472 --> 30:49.556
and he's meeting me
like this,

30:49.639 --> 30:53.268
with tubes in me and my hair
all gross and matted.

30:53.351 --> 30:55.228
[sighs]

30:55.312 --> 30:56.480
Tami, he doesn't care.

30:56.563 --> 30:57.981
He just wants to see his mom,
you know?

31:02.360 --> 31:03.487
And it's gonna hurt
to hold him.

31:03.570 --> 31:05.781
Maybe not.

31:05.864 --> 31:07.074
Want to say hi, Fred?

31:07.157 --> 31:09.409
Fred?

31:09.493 --> 31:10.702
I thought we were
naming him Gabriel.

31:10.786 --> 31:11.995
Well, then you shouldn't
have been

31:12.079 --> 31:15.665
under general anesthesia then,
should ya?

31:15.749 --> 31:17.167
‐ Here.
‐ Okay.

31:17.250 --> 31:19.252
‐ You got him.
‐ Ow. Ow.

31:19.336 --> 31:20.420
She's got you.
She's got you.

31:20.504 --> 31:21.088
Wait.
Ow‐‐ow. No.

31:21.171 --> 31:21.755
Not there.
It hurts.

31:21.838 --> 31:22.756
Fuck.
Everything hurts.

31:22.839 --> 31:25.092
‐ Okay, okay, all right.
‐ Ah. Fuck.

31:25.175 --> 31:28.095
Nurse, could she get something
for the pain, please?

31:28.178 --> 31:29.513
She's on something.

31:29.596 --> 31:30.013
Maximum something.

31:37.395 --> 31:39.064
Tell me about you.

31:39.147 --> 31:42.234
You know, distract me.

31:42.317 --> 31:44.236
I'm good.

31:44.319 --> 31:45.487
Yeah, yeah.
Things are great.

31:48.323 --> 31:51.743
I was thinking we might need a
hand with childcare, you know.

31:51.827 --> 31:54.162
Just so I can get
some overtime at work.

31:54.246 --> 31:56.998
Why?

31:57.082 --> 31:59.000
Just 'cause he costs
a lot of money.

31:59.084 --> 32:00.544
I don't know when you're gonna
be back up on your feet,

32:00.627 --> 32:01.753
doing hair again and stuff.

32:01.837 --> 32:03.755
Uh, we‐‐yeah, we do.

32:03.839 --> 32:05.173
It's gonna be soon.
Right, Raquelle?

32:05.257 --> 32:07.008
Hopefully, honey.
Hopefully real soon.

32:08.760 --> 32:12.472
<i>♪ upbeat Latin music ♪</i>

32:12.556 --> 32:14.850
<i>♪♪♪</i>

32:14.933 --> 32:17.978
<i>[singing in Spanish]</i>

32:18.061 --> 32:22.941
<i>♪♪♪</i>

32:23.024 --> 32:25.986
[indistinct chatter in Spanish]

32:26.778 --> 32:27.737
[Anne]
How's it going?

32:27.821 --> 32:30.699
Oh, you know,
I'm crushing it.

32:32.826 --> 32:34.161
[speaking Spanish]

32:38.331 --> 32:40.292
They're just admiring
your handiwork!

32:40.375 --> 32:41.710
Oh, yeah?
Thank you.

32:41.793 --> 32:42.836
‐ Mucho gracias.
‐ [laughs]

32:42.919 --> 32:46.339
So these people
all related to you?

32:46.423 --> 32:47.674
Three generations, yeah.

32:47.757 --> 32:50.844
We're like
a street‐food conglomerate.

32:50.927 --> 32:52.429
They all look like they
really like each other.

32:52.512 --> 32:54.764
They do.
Weird, huh?

32:54.848 --> 32:56.516
Well, I gotta get back
to the mole.

32:56.600 --> 32:57.767
But you're doing great.

32:57.851 --> 32:58.685
Just hang in there, okay?

32:58.768 --> 32:59.769
We take a break at 8:00 p. m.

32:59.853 --> 33:00.812
Awesome.
What time is it?

33:00.896 --> 33:01.855
[Anne]
3:30.

33:04.441 --> 33:05.984
[speaks Spanish]

33:06.067 --> 33:07.736
[laughter]

33:07.819 --> 33:09.321
Thank you.
Appreciate that. Mucho!

33:21.541 --> 33:23.835
[Mikey] The colors.
The textures, Frank.

33:23.919 --> 33:27.589
<i>♪ laidback rock music ♪</i>

33:27.672 --> 33:31.968
<i>♪♪♪</i>

33:32.052 --> 33:36.097
‐ You get the fragrances, yeah?
‐ Okay.

33:36.181 --> 33:37.265
I'll get the shoes
and the dresses.

33:39.643 --> 33:40.852
[Liam]
MaVar, over here!

33:46.149 --> 33:47.776
No.

33:47.859 --> 33:48.276
No.

33:51.321 --> 33:52.405
'Sup?

33:52.489 --> 33:53.782
‐ You ready?
‐ Yeah.

33:53.865 --> 33:55.575
Let me introduce you
to my friend, Veronica.

33:55.659 --> 33:57.619
MaVar, V.

33:57.702 --> 33:59.454
Veronica, MaVar.

33:59.537 --> 34:01.748
Var and V!

34:01.831 --> 34:02.874
I'm V.
You're Var.

34:02.958 --> 34:04.292
‐ Lots of Vs.
‐ Yeah.

34:04.376 --> 34:06.336
I'm going to a sporting event
with you?

34:06.419 --> 34:07.712
It's nice to meet you, V.

34:07.796 --> 34:09.256
Ooh.

34:09.339 --> 34:11.549
Look at you
with your strong handshake!

34:11.633 --> 34:12.467
You know, I work out.

34:12.550 --> 34:14.052
What's up, man?

34:14.135 --> 34:15.262
I'm Kevin.

34:15.345 --> 34:16.554
Are you gay, yes or no?

34:16.638 --> 34:18.014
Uh...
Hey, Kev.

34:18.098 --> 34:19.849
No, I'm not gay.

34:19.933 --> 34:21.768
Though people think
that because, you know,

34:21.851 --> 34:23.103
I'm an activist for
the LGBTQ community.

34:23.186 --> 34:25.063
You know, I help them
with the parade,

34:25.146 --> 34:27.274
provide fancy convertibles
and such.

34:27.357 --> 34:28.400
‐ You guys ready to roll?
‐ [both] Yeah.

34:28.483 --> 34:30.151
Uh, no, V,

34:30.235 --> 34:32.445
you can't go anymore
because of that thing.

34:32.529 --> 34:34.823
What thing?

34:34.906 --> 34:35.865
The thing that I need
to discuss with you

34:35.949 --> 34:37.867
for a moment over here,

34:37.951 --> 34:39.327
away from the linebacker.

34:39.411 --> 34:41.121
Oh, man, I'm much too big
to be a linebacker.

34:41.204 --> 34:42.622
But I did play basketball
at Georgetown.

34:42.706 --> 34:44.332
Oh!
Is that right?

34:44.416 --> 34:46.584
Okay, this is not what
I meant by a new friend.

34:46.668 --> 34:48.878
I meant a girlfriend
or a very gay man.

34:48.962 --> 34:50.588
Oh, please.
I'm in love with you.

34:50.672 --> 34:52.048
There's nobody
gonna change that, baby.

34:52.132 --> 34:54.050
Guys ready to go?
Go, Sox!

34:54.134 --> 34:55.051
[MaVar] All right, here we go.
Hey.

34:55.135 --> 34:56.303
Pleasure meeting
you, Kevin!

34:56.386 --> 34:57.596
Yeah, you too, buddy!

35:02.017 --> 35:03.351
All right, quick.

35:03.435 --> 35:06.396
Tell me how I find
a new best friend for my wife.

35:10.942 --> 35:13.361
[line trilling]

35:13.445 --> 35:15.071
[Lip] <i>Yo, it's Lip.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

35:15.155 --> 35:16.114
<i>[phone beeps]</i>

35:17.949 --> 35:18.908
[inmate]
Hey, dick!

35:18.992 --> 35:19.868
[Ian] Sorry.
I'll be quick.

35:19.951 --> 35:22.412
[inmate]
One call each!

35:22.495 --> 35:23.705
‐ [phone rings]
‐ Hello?

35:23.788 --> 35:24.372
[recorded voice]
<i>Collect call from‐‐</i>

35:24.456 --> 35:27.834
Yes, I accept the charges.

35:27.917 --> 35:29.628
Hey, Ian. What's up?

35:29.711 --> 35:31.963
[Ian] <i>Hey, Debs.</i>
<i>Do you know where Lip is?</i>

35:32.047 --> 35:33.506
<i>I couldn't get a hold of him,</i>

35:33.590 --> 35:36.843
and, you know, I could really
use some advice right now.

35:36.926 --> 35:37.469
[Debbie]
<i>Oh, I think he's probably</i>

35:37.552 --> 35:38.136
<i>still at the hospital.</i>

35:38.219 --> 35:40.930
No way.
Is Tami in labor?

35:41.014 --> 35:42.432
She had the baby.

35:42.515 --> 35:44.017
The whole thing's
fucked up.

35:44.100 --> 35:46.436
Tami almost died.
She's still in the hospital.

35:46.519 --> 35:47.145
Lip's up shit's creek trying

35:47.228 --> 35:48.938
to handle the newborn alone.

35:49.022 --> 35:50.231
It's a hot mess.

35:50.315 --> 35:51.691
[Ian]
<i>But the baby's all right?</i>

35:52.734 --> 35:53.610
<i>Debs?</i>

35:53.693 --> 35:54.611
<i>Debbie?</i>

35:54.694 --> 35:56.738
No.

35:56.821 --> 35:57.364
[Ian]
<i>Debbie, can you hear me?</i>

35:57.447 --> 35:58.531
‐ No!
‐ [Ian] Hello?

35:58.615 --> 35:59.532
No!

35:59.616 --> 36:01.534
No!
No!

36:03.161 --> 36:05.830
What's with you?

36:05.914 --> 36:07.874
Lip had the baby.

36:07.957 --> 36:09.125
Oh, yeah?

36:09.209 --> 36:10.627
Boy or girl?

36:10.710 --> 36:13.672
I don't know.
We got cut off.

36:13.755 --> 36:14.923
Something's wrong.

36:15.006 --> 36:17.926
Tami's still in the hospital.

36:18.009 --> 36:20.637
Lip's all alone with the baby.

36:20.720 --> 36:23.223
Well, congrats.
You're an uncle.

36:23.306 --> 36:25.684
I already was.

36:25.767 --> 36:28.061
All right, then.

36:38.321 --> 36:39.906
Stop the tape.

36:39.989 --> 36:43.243
There.
Can you zoom in?

36:43.326 --> 36:46.746
[scoffs]
Those motherfuckers.

36:46.830 --> 36:50.458
Then they return with a dolly
at 016:00 hours.

36:50.542 --> 36:51.251
Sorry I missed it.

36:51.334 --> 36:53.294
I nap from one to three,
usually.

